Class:
=====
Class is a blueprint or template for object
Object:
======
A physical existance of class

Class define:
============
class name_of_class:
	'''doc string'''
	properties(variables)
	actions(Methos)


class Person:
    def __init__(self):
        self.name = "Ashok"
        self.age = 25
    
    def say_hello(self):
        print("My name:",self.name)
        print("My age:",self.age)
A=Person()
print(A.name)
print(A.age)


-->Here A is reference varibale 
-->Person() is object
